## 4. Implementation Roadmap

### Phase 1 — Foundation (Days 1–2)

- [x] **Install Vitest** + `@testing-library/react` + `jsdom`
- [x] Configure `vitest.config.ts` with Next.js path aliases
- [x] Add `test:unit` and `test:unit:coverage` scripts to `package.json`
- [x] Write unit tests for `lib/rbac.ts` (18 tests) — highest value, pure logic
- [x] Write unit tests for `lib/api-client.ts` (12 tests)
- [x] Write unit tests for `lib/use-stored-role.ts` (4 tests)

### Phase 2 — Core E2E Coverage (Days 3–5)

- [x] Extend a11y audit to staff, portal, and admin routes (45 tests)
- [x] Add RBAC enforcement E2E tests (8 tests)
- [x] Add data-driven tests for `/staff/dashboard` (3 tests)
- [x] Add data-driven tests for `/staff/medical-records/[id]/edit` (4 tests)
- [x] Add data-driven tests for `/staff/nurse-intake` (3 tests)
- [x] Add data-driven tests for `/staff/vital-signs` (3 tests)
- [x] Add data-driven tests for `/admin/dashboard` (3 tests)
- [x] Add data-driven tests for `/admin/users` + `users/[id]` (7 tests)
- [x] Add data-driven tests for `/portal/records` (3 tests)
- [x] Add data-driven tests for `/portal/appointments` (5 tests)
- [x] Create Page Object Models for: `DashboardPage`, `AdminUsersPage`, `QueuePage`

### Phase 3 — Complete Page Coverage (Days 6–8)

- [x] Unit tests for `lib/staff-queue.ts` (10 tests)
- [x] Unit tests for `lib/operations-api.ts` (8 tests)
- [x] Unit tests for `lib/clinical-api.ts` (8 tests)
- [x] Data-driven tests for remaining staff pages (closures, schedule, slots, booking wizard, pricing, revenue, invoices)
- [x] Data-driven tests for remaining admin pages (departments, rooms, appointments, news, public-content)
- [x] Data-driven tests for remaining portal pages (messages, profile, billing, lab-results)

### Phase 4 — Specialized & Polish (Days 9–10)

- [ ] Visual regression baselines for new routes (7 tests)
- [ ] Extended responsive tests (18 tests)
- [ ] SEO audit spec (6 tests)
- [ ] Performance/Lighthouse spec (5 tests)
- [ ] Security smoke spec (5 tests)
- [ ] Multi-browser support: add Firefox and WebKit projects to Playwright config

